@{b}@{u}6.3.  HRControl - The universal commodity to drive ProBench v3.0@{uu}@{ub}

HRControl is a little commodity which contains some usefull functions to drive ProBench. It was created for the socalled "Power User" and should be only used when it is well known which consequences can arise from its use.

If  you are a user  who wants to take advantage from all functions of ProBench3, HRControl perfectly fits your needs.

@{u}Functions:@{uu}

HRControl is driven through hotkeys like most of the commodities. These hotkeys are set through ToolTypes (TT:) and shoud be chosen not to collide with other hotkeys in use.

HRControl uses LCOMMAND LSHIFT as a standard qualifier as well as the left amiga key plus the left alt key. Furthermore you have to hit another key to use the functins like:

@{b}a@{ub} puts monitorswitch on the amiga display status (TT: AMIGA)

@{b}b@{ub} puts monitorswitch on the merlin display (TT: BOARD)

@{b}t@{ub} toggles monitorswitch status (TT: TOGGLE)

@{b}k@{ub} closes the upper merlin screen (Be carefull !) (TT: KILL)

@{b}DEL@{ub} puts monitorswitch in visible switching (see ModeMaster) (TT: BSWITCH)

@{b}2@{ub} puts the scrren palette on the standard digitizer palette (TT: PALETTE2)

@{b}F1@{ub} grabs the upper screen in XPGI format (TT: GRABXPGI)

@{b}F2@{ub} grabs the upper screen in ILBM format (TT: GRABILBM)

@{b}F6@{ub} copies hidden parts of the upper screen into the videoram and considerably iprooves speed. (TT: UPRECTS)

@{b}F7@{ub} converts the upper screen from 8 to 16 bits, this is only possible if you have a 16 bit mode with the same resolution of the actual screen. (TT: DOXGA)

@{b}F8@{ub} does the opposite conversion done by F7. If on the 16 bit screen there is a 24 bit resolution working in 8 bit could be much slower.  (TT: UNDOXGA)

The last two functions should be only temporarily used

@{b}F9@{ub} Empties the video ram and loads on board the upper screen. In this case you can avoid a memory fragmentation (TT: FLUSHMEM)

@{b}F10@{ub} Loads the upper screen on the bord. This has meaning only if a program has to do its task always in the video ram. You shouldn't use this funcion with the digitizer. (TT: FIXSCREEN)
@endnode

@node "4. ProSpeed3" "4. ProSpeed 3"
@font topaz 8
@wordwrap
@prev "3. HRControl"
@toc "ProBench3"

@{u}6.4. ProSpeed3@{uu}

This is the new version compatible with ProBench v3.0. ProSpeed accellerates drawing of background patterns defined in WBPattern. To obtain this you must convert gaphics for IPrefs from planar to chunky. Due to technical reasons the original bitmap cannot be freely kept in CHIP RAM.

To install ProSpeed3 add this line @{b}BEFORE@{ub} IPrefs in you startup-sequence:

run <>NIL: ProSpeed3

This program returned to be usefull because not everybody is willing to work with disadvantages of picture.datatype v43 by Ralph Schmitt.
@endnode

